question_title: Will the US government enter a shutdown before February 1, 2026?
summary: This is a definitional question about a past event. Today is February 4, 2026. Multiple credible sources confirm that the US government entered a partial shutdown at midnight on January 31, 2026 (before February 1, 2026), and this shutdown resulted in furloughs of federal employees - more than 10,000 FAA workers and approximately 8,000 State Department employees. The shutdown lasted four days until the House voted 217-214 on February 3 to end it. All resolution criteria are clearly met. The small residual uncertainty accounts for potential edge cases in resolution interpretation or question annulment.

factors.description: Shutdown definitively began January 31, 2026 at midnight - before February 1, 2026 deadline
Federal employees were furloughed (10,000+ FAA, ~8,000 State Dept) - meets 'shutdown furlough' requirement
Multiple credible sources (NPR, ABC, CBS, Government Executive) report consistent facts
Shutdown was 'four-day old' when ended Feb 3, confirming Jan 31 start date
Potential uncertainty in resolution source interpretation or question annulment clause
